comIsValidHandle            package:rcom            R Documentation

_C_h_e_c_k _i_f _t_h_e _C_O_M _o_b_j_e_c_t _i_s _v_a_l_i_d

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Check if the passed object is a valid COM object

_U_s_a_g_e:

     comIsValidHandle(handle)

_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

  handle: COM object (class "COMObject") as returned by e.g.
          'comCreateObject'

_V_a_l_u_e:

     'com.isvalid' returns 'TRUE' if the object is valid, 'FALSE'
     otherwise.

_A_u_t_h_o_r(_s):

     Thomas Baier

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o:

     'comCreateObject', 'comGetObject'

